properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 8:36AM CST until January 9 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...A WINTRY MIX OF PRECIPITATION EXPECTED TODAY...

.A Winter Weather Advisory is in effect for counties in western
Wisconsin east of Hudson, to Durand for a combination of freezing
drizzle and light snow on today.

A storm system will move from the Central Plains, northeast
across the Upper Midwest by this afternoon. Light precipitation
in the form of mostly freezing drizzle with some snow mixed in,
will develop this morning, and continue through the early
afternoon before temperatures rise above freezing. A light glaze
of ice and less than a half inch of snow are likely. This will
cause area roads to become hazardous.

* WHAT...Freezing drizzle. Additional ice accumulations of a
light glaze.

* WHERE...Pepin and Eau Claire Counties.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 3 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling. Prepare for possible
power outages.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
